@startuml
title Schedule Manager Use Case Diagram

left to right direction
skinparam linetype polyline

actor "Student" as Student

rectangle "Schedule Manager" as System {
  rectangle " " as ColLeft {
    usecase "Add Personal Schedule" as UC_AddPersonal
    usecase "Import Student Courses" as UC_ImportStudent
    usecase "Import Professor Office Hours" as UC_ImportProfessor
    usecase "View Schedule" as UC_ViewSchedule
    usecase "Calculate Available Time" as UC_CalcAvailable
  }
  rectangle " " as ColRight {
    usecase "Select CSV File" as UC_SelectCSV
    usecase "Show Weekly View" as UC_ShowWeekView
    usecase "Data Validation / Conflict Detection" as UC_Validation
    usecase "Show Details" as UC_ShowDetails
    usecase "Delete Schedule" as UC_DeleteSchedule
    usecase "Open Mail Client" as UC_OpenMailClient
  }
}

Student --> UC_AddPersonal
Student --> UC_ImportStudent
Student --> UC_ImportProfessor
Student --> UC_ViewSchedule
Student --> UC_CalcAvailable

UC_ImportStudent ..> UC_SelectCSV : <<include>>
UC_ImportProfessor ..> UC_SelectCSV : <<include>>
UC_ViewSchedule ..> UC_ShowWeekView : <<include>>

' Always run validation before add/import
UC_AddPersonal ..> UC_Validation : <<include>>
UC_ImportStudent ..> UC_Validation : <<include>>
UC_ImportProfessor ..> UC_Validation : <<include>>

' Conditional extensions
UC_ShowDetails ..> UC_ViewSchedule : <<extend>>
UC_DeleteSchedule ..> UC_ViewSchedule : <<extend>>
UC_OpenMailClient ..> UC_CalcAvailable : <<extend>>
 

note right of UC_Validation
Always runs before add/import; checks overlap and data consistency
end note

 

note right of UC_ShowDetails
Double-click an event in weekly view to see details
end note

note right of UC_DeleteSchedule
Right-click an event and choose "Delete"
end note

note right of UC_OpenMailClient
Double-click teacher email to open the default mail client
end note

@enduml